Playlist.description: A *playlist* resource represents a YouTube playlist. A playlist is a collection of videos that can be viewed sequentially and shared with other users. A playlist can contain up to 200 videos, and YouTube does not limit the number of playlists that each user creates. By default, playlists are publicly visible to other users, but playlists can be public or private. YouTube also uses playlists to identify special collections of videos for a channel, such as: - uploaded videos - favorite videos - positively rated (liked) videos - watch history - watch later To be more specific, these lists are associated with a channel, which is a collection of a person, group, or company's videos, playlists, and other YouTube information. You can retrieve the playlist IDs for each of these lists from the channel resource for a given channel. You can then use the playlistItems.list method to retrieve any of those lists. You can also add or remove items from those lists by calling the playlistItems.insert and playlistItems.delete methods.

scheduledEndTime.description: The time that the broadcast is scheduled to end. The value is specified in ISO 8601 format. If the value is empty or the property is not present, then the broadcast is scheduled to continue indefinitely.

concurrentViewers.description: The number of viewers currently watching the broadcast. The property and its value will be present if the broadcast has current viewers and the broadcast owner has not hidden the viewcount for the video. Note that YouTube stops tracking the number of concurrent viewers for a broadcast when the broadcast ends. So, this property would not identify the number of viewers watching an archived video of a live broadcast that already ended.

actualEndTime.description: The time that the broadcast actually ended. The value is specified in ISO 8601 format. This value will not be available until the broadcast is over.

scheduledStartTime.description: The time that the broadcast is scheduled to begin. The value is specified in ISO 8601 format.

activeLiveChatId.description: The ID of the currently active live chat attached to this video. This field is filled only if the video is a currently live broadcast that has live chat. Once the broadcast transitions to complete this field will be removed and the live chat closed down. For persistent broadcasts that live chat id will no longer be tied to this video but rather to the new video being displayed at the persistent page.

actualStartTime.description: The time that the broadcast actually started. The value is specified in ISO 8601 format. This value will not be available until the broadcast begins.

lastUpdated.description: The date and time when the caption track was last updated. The value is specified in ISO 8601 format.

isLarge.description: Indicates whether the caption track uses large text for the vision-impaired. The default value is false.

language.description: The language of the caption track. The property value is a BCP-47 language tag.

isDraft.description: Indicates whether the caption track is a draft. If the value is true, then the track is not publicly visible. The default value is false. @mutable youtube.captions.insert youtube.captions.update

name.description: The name of the caption track. The name is intended to be visible to the user as an option during playback.

isAutoSynced.description: Indicates whether YouTube synchronized the caption track to the audio track in the video. The value will be true if a sync was explicitly requested when the caption track was uploaded. For example, when calling the captions.insert or captions.update methods, you can set the sync parameter to true to instruct YouTube to sync the uploaded track to the video. If the value is false, YouTube uses the time codes in the uploaded caption track to determine when to display captions.

isCC.description: Indicates whether the track contains closed captions for the deaf and hard of hearing. The default value is false.

failureReason.description: The reason that YouTube failed to process the caption track. This property is only present if the state property's value is failed.

isEasyReader.description: Indicates whether caption track is formatted for "easy reader," meaning it is at a third-grade level for language learners. The default value is false.

videoId.description: The ID that YouTube uses to uniquely identify the video associated with the caption track. @mutable youtube.captions.insert

audioTrackType.description: The type of audio track associated with the caption track.
